Avangardco Net Income Advances 38% in 2010 as Output Gains

-- B y   A m a n d a   J o r d a n   a n d   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-03-04T07:54:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/avangardco-net-income-advances-38-in-2010-as-output-gains-1-.html
  Avangardco Investments Public Ltd. (AVGR) ,
Ukraine’s largest egg producer, said net profit jumped 38
percent last year as the company increased production.  Net income advanced to $184.758 million in 2010 from
$133.669 million the previous year, the Kiev-based company said
in a statement today. Eggs output increased 22 percent to 4.4
million units and poultry flock jumped to 24.3 million from 16.1
million, according to the statement.  Avangardco invested $82.1 million in 2010, most of which
was used to build two new plants that are scheduled to be up and
running by the end of this year.  “The company expects further growth in sales” this year
Avangardco said, adding that it plans to start exports to  Russia 
in 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
